              <h2>How does Hyper-V work?</h2>
              <p>Hyper-V is a thin layer of software between the hardware and the Operating System (OS) that allows multiple instances of an OS to run, unmodified, on a single physical server at the same time. This technology is an ideal platform for developing and testing software, consolidating production servers, and managing business continuity (growth and scalability).</p>
